The US Air Force flew two reconnaissance missions over eastern Ukraine this week, the first on December 27 just a few days after Russia said it would withdraw 10,000 troops from the shared border, CNN reported.

More on the leaders’ call:
- Ukraine has been a point of contention for the two countries since the annexation of Crimea in 2014, Al Jazeera reports

- Russia denied a new assault on Ukraine during the previous conversation and warned against any NATO military involvement, according to Reuters and Al Jazeera

address climate change coming out of the conference as well as former MP Owen Paterson's recent resignation following allegations of financial corruption. 

- On climate change, Johnson said "We've got to be honest, the COP 26 summit here in Glasgow is not going to fix it in one go. We're not going to arrest climate change right here, right now. That is just impossible. And and I think everybody has got to be realistic about that."
